Science in Pajamas

As week two of mandatory remote work draws to a close, it seems as good a time as any to revive this blog and start talking about research and life since that piece about climbing in the future. I have been a predoctoral fellow at the Center for Astrophysics | Harvard & Smithsonian (stylized as dictated by the powers that be) for about a year and a half now. It has been an amazing experience that has allowed me to travel more in the past year than I have in the rest of my life combined. 
